DEPENDENCIES
------------

+ Debian packages:

# apt-get install <package>

	+ perl
	+ perl-modules
	+ sudo
	+ iproute
	+ iptables
	+ apache
	+ libapache-mod-perl
	+ liblog-dispatch-perl
	+ liblog-log4perl-perl
	+ libhtml-template-perl
	+ liblocale-gettext-perl
	+ libxml-xerces-perl
	+ libxml-simple-perl
	+ libxml-xpath-perl
	+ libnetwork-ipv4addr-perl
	+ liberror-perl
	+ libdevel-stacktrace-perl
	+ libapache-authcookie-perl
	+ gettext

+ modules from cpan

# cpan <module>

	+ HTML::Template::Expr
	+ Locale::TextDomain
	+ Net::Ifconfig::Wrapper
	+ Net::IPv4Addr
	+ Sys::Hostname
	+ Sys::Load
	+ Sys::CPU
	+ Apache::Singleton

Some modules require gcc, make and libc6-dev.


INSTALATION
-----------

1.- Configure:

    If apache is not going to listen on port 80 change it in
    conf/firewall.xml.in before running configure.

    $ ./configure <arguments>

    Accepts standard GNU configure arguments, run ./configure --help
    for a list

    Apache is autodetected

    Suggested argument: --localstatedir=/var , to have variable data
    installed in /var

2.- Instalation, as root:

    $ make install

3.- Allow the apache user to run root commands via sudo:

    run "visudo" and add the this line to the end of the file:

    www-data        ALL=NOPASSWD: ALL

4.- Restart apache:

    /etc/init.d/apache restart

5.- To make ebox run on startup:

    ln -s /etc/init.d/ebox /etc/rc2.d/S99ebox

6.- Give write permission to the apache user (www-data) in the
    localstatedir directory: $prefix/var/ebox or /var/ebox if the
    --localstatedir=/var parameter was used:

    chown -R www-data.www-data /var/ebox

RUNNING
-------

The url for the administration interface is:

http://<ip address>:<apache-port>/ebox/

The default password is 'lala'. It may be changed in the general configuration
page.

Ebox logs are located in $localstatedir/ebox/log/ (localstatedir will be
$prefix/var by default or, usually, /var).

Some errors may be found in the apache error log: /var/log/apache/error.log
